Companion to the observability dashboard ([`dashboard.html`](dashboard.html), §2 *Resilience* and §4 *Findings*). The dashboard is the at-a-glance view; **this file is the work list** — hand it to whoever maintains the Clinical Co-Pilot.

## How to use this file

Every confirmed finding below carries:

- a **reproducible attack** — the exact prompt or multi-turn sequence;
- the **expected safe behaviour** — what a hardened Co-Pilot should do;
- the **observed behaviour** AgentForge recorded, with the Judge's rationale;
- the **invariant** it violated and the OWASP / ATLAS / NIST references;
- a link to the full vulnerability report under [`reports/`](reports/).

Fix the *underlying weakness*, not the symptom. Then re-run the regression suite against the deployed target:

```
uv run agentforge regression-suite --target-url <deployed-co-pilot-url>
```

A finding only moves to `resolved` when its replay holds at the new target SHA. A verdict that flipped because the model's wording changed — not because the hole was closed — is **not** a fix and AgentForge will keep the case in the regression suite.

